The paper proposes a compressive sensing-based joint channel estimation scheme for FDD massive MIMO, which involves exploiting the spatio-temporal common sparsity of MIMO channels. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SI), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Machine Learning (cs.MM), and Learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on compressive sensing and channel estimation, cs.IT and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
